<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
            <title>MAIN CASE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the input shaft. Next, coat the bearing cap sealing surface with purple Loctite
                    515 or the equivalent. Slide the bearing cap into place (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022h8">Figure 178</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13022h8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13022h8" filename="../figg13/G13022H8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 178. Install Input Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>Tighten the cap bolts to 34 to 41 ft-lbs. (46 to 56 N&#183; m).</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use a sleeve to protect the cap seal during cap installation.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the neutral safety switch if the unit is equipped with one (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022h9">Figure 179</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022h9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022h9" filename="../figg13/G13022H9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 179. Neutral Safety Switch</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 5th speed gear with the thrust face toward the input bearing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i0">Figure 180</hotlnk>). The timing marks should be positioned to align with
                    the countershafts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022i0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022i0" filename="../figg13/G13022I0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 180. Timing Marks Aligned With Countershafts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the 4th-5th speed fork (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13022i1">Figure 181</hotlnk>). Secure it with the pin and two snap rings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13022i1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13022i1" filename="../figg13/G13022I1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 181. 4th - 5th Speed Fork</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always wear safety glasses to help protect your eyes against flying parts.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
